snippet.textDisplay:
If you can't handle your favorite fighter taking a loss without you're own precious ego being affected and then ultimately turn on them perhaps you're not mature enough to be a fan of the sport.

Everyone loves a winner but these fighters aren't infallible beings, they're just humans. Connor McGregor is an amazing showman and a great fighter. When he hypes up a fight its a lot of fun to watch. Doesn't mean you have to feel like a fool for believing in him if he happens to suffer a loss. Unless you're basing your fandom solely on win streaks alone. Then I'd argue you're a fickle person.

We should Just appreciate that we have great entertainers in the sport still willing to put it all on the line.
